# plotting helpers

def calc_regression(x, y):
    m, b, r, _, __ = stats.linregress(x, y)
    return m, b, r ** 2

def plot_points_regression(ax, x, y, pos="lower right"):
    m, b, r2 = calc_regression(x, y)
    ax.scatter(x, y, alpha=0.3)
    ax.plot(x, x * m + b, color="r")
    ax.legend([f'r² ≈ {r2*100:.2f}%'], loc=pos)

def set_labels(ax, x, y, ignorey=False):
    ax.set_xlabel(x, fontweight="bold")
    if not ignorey:
        ax.set_ylabel(y, fontweight="bold")

def clean_axis(ax):
    ax.set_xticks([])
    ax.set_yticks([])
    for side in ["top", "bottom", "left", "right"]:
        ax.spines[side].set_visible(False)

def cite_source(fig):
    fig.text(
        0.5, 0.0,
        "Data from nflfastr, 2016-2020, including postseason. Limited to rushes and passes (including scrambles).\nExcludes PATs, kneels, spikes, garbage time, & plays involving penalties, replays, or challenges. © Chris Shields 2021",
        va="bottom", ha="center"
    )

def init_plot(title, n=1):
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, n, figsize=(8 * n, 8), sharey=True)
    fig.suptitle(title, fontsize=13, fontweight="bold")
    return fig, axs

def save_plot(name):
    plt.savefig(f'imgs/{name}.png', facecolor="w")

def text_arrow(ax, msg, x, y, xtext, ytext):
    ax.annotate(msg, xy=(x,y), xytext=(xtext,ytext), arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle="->"))

data = df.groupby(["season", "posteam"])

y = data["epa"].mean()
xs = [
    ("Order In Subsequent Draft", data["draft_order"].mean()),
    ("Season Win %", data["pos_wins"].mean())
]

fig, axs = init_plot("Offensive EPA/play is a good measure of a team's performance", 2)
for i, (lbl, x) in enumerate(xs):
    plot_points_regression(axs[i], x, y)
    set_labels(axs[i], lbl, "Off. EPA/Play (per game)", i != 0)
    clean_axis(axs[i])
    if i == 0:
        text_arrow(axs[i], "2018 KC", 0.92, 0.2925, 1, 0.27)
        text_arrow(axs[i], "2018 ARI", 0.02, -0.245, 0.025, -0.3)
        text_arrow(axs[i], "2020 HOU", 0.065, 0.1, 0.09, 0.125)
        text_arrow(axs[i], "2019 PIT", 0.56, -0.1575, 0.65, -0.175)
cite_source(fig)

full_data = df.groupby(["game_id", "posteam"])
pass_ratio_data = full_data["pass_or_scramble"].mean().reset_index()
rush_heavy = pass_ratio_data[pass_ratio_data["pass_or_scramble"] < 0.5].reset_index()

def is_rush_heavy(rows):
    row = rows.iloc[0]
    return (
        (rush_heavy["game_id"] == row["game_id"]) &
        (rush_heavy["posteam"] == row["posteam"])
    ).any()

data = full_data.filter(is_rush_heavy)
pass_data = data[data["pass_or_scramble"]].groupby(["game_id", "posteam"])
data = data.groupby(["game_id", "posteam"])

x = pass_data["epa"].mean()
y = data["epa"].mean()

fig, ax = init_plot("Even rush-heavy offenses are defined by the pass")
plot_points_regression(ax, x, y)
set_labels(ax, "EPA/Pass\n(teams that rushed more than they passed)", "Off. EPA/Play")
clean_axis(ax)
cite_source(fig)
text_arrow(ax, "PIT, vs CLE, 2020 WC", -1, -1.1, -1, -1.25)
text_arrow(ax, "LAC, vs PIT, 2019 W6", -0.65, -0.975, -0.375, -1)
text_arrow(ax, "PIT, vs CAR, 2018 W10", 2.35, 1.225, 2.325, 1.125)
text_arrow(ax, "BAL, vs MIA, 2019 W1", 2.8, 1.5, 1.4, 1.5)

pass_data = df[df["pass_or_scramble"]]
rush_data = df[~df["pass_or_scramble"]]

xs = (
    pass_data["epa"],
    rush_data["epa"]
)

fig, ax = init_plot("Passing EPA has greater mean & variance than rushing EPA")

plt.axvline(xs[0].mean(), linestyle="--", color="lightsteelblue")
plt.axvline(xs[1].mean(), linestyle="--", color="lightsalmon")
sns.kdeplot(xs[0], ax=ax)
sns.kdeplot(xs[1], ax=ax)
ax.legend([
    f"Average Pass (μ ≈ {xs[0].mean():.4f})",
    f"Average Rush (μ ≈ {xs[1].mean():.4f})",
    f"Pass (σ² ≈ {np.var(xs[0]):.4f})",
    f"Rush (σ² ≈ {np.var(xs[1]):.4f})"
])

set_labels(ax, "EPA", "Likelihood")
clean_axis(ax)
cite_source(fig)

In [11]:
data = df[df["pass_or_scramble"]].groupby(["game_id", "posteam"])["epa"].mean().reset_index()

def get_pass_epa_diff(row):
    data2 = data[data["game_id"] == row["game_id"]]
    cond = data2["posteam"] == row["posteam"]
    my_epa = data2[cond]["epa"].values[0]
    their_epa = data2[~cond]["epa"].values[0]
    return my_epa - their_epa
data["pass_epa_diff"] = data.apply(get_pass_epa_diff, axis=1)

data = df.merge(data, on=["game_id", "posteam"]).groupby(["season", "posteam"])
y = data["pass_epa_diff"].mean()
xs = (
    ("Order In Subsequent Draft", data["draft_order"].mean()),
    ("Season Win %", data["pos_wins"].mean())
)

fig, axs = init_plot("Passing better than your opponent is an even better measure of team performance than offensive EPA/play", 2)
for i, (lbl, x) in enumerate(xs):
    plot_points_regression(axs[i], x, y)
    set_labels(axs[i], lbl, "EPA/Pass Differential", i != 0)
    clean_axis(axs[i])
    if i == 0:
        text_arrow(axs[i], "17 CLE, 19 WAS,\n20 JAX, 19 CIN", 0.075, -0.375, 0.15, -0.42)
        text_arrow(axs[i], "2016 NE", 0.99, 0.36, 0.8, 0.36)
        text_arrow(axs[i], "2017 LAC", 0.51, 0.27, 0.375, 0.3125)
cite_source(fig)

data = df.groupby(["game_id", "posteam"])["epa"].mean().reset_index()
def get_epa_diff(row):
    data2 = data[data["game_id"] == row["game_id"]]
    cond = data2["posteam"] == row["posteam"]
    my_epa = data2[cond]["epa"].values[0]
    their_epa = data2[~cond]["epa"].values[0]
    return my_epa - their_epa
    
data["epa_diff"] = data.apply(get_epa_diff, axis=1)

data = df.merge(data, on=["game_id", "posteam"]).groupby(["season", "posteam"])
y = data["epa_diff"].mean()
xs = (
    ("Order In Subsequent Draft", data["draft_order"].mean()),
    ("Season Win %", data["pos_wins"].mean())
)

fig, axs = init_plot("Having trouble winning football games? Try playing better than your opponent", 2)
for i, (lbl, x) in enumerate(xs):
    plot_points_regression(axs[i], x, y)
    set_labels(axs[i], lbl, "Off. EPA/Play Differential", i != 0)
    clean_axis(axs[i])
